# Day 24 Scratch &mdash; Games

First, let's explore the fourteenth lesson in the unit. To begin, find your ECS Version 5 curriculum and open to page 178-182.

[Access a Digital Copy of the lesson>>](http://code.org/ecs#page=178)

## Key Concepts

Students investigate two different types of games by customizing sprites, adding another sprite that gives you 2 points and getting the game to stop at 10 points or more by telling you that you won..

## Common Difficulties

Some students may struggle a bit with the variable and conditional blocks used in these games.  It is suggested to have the students work in pairs to complete the monkey and pinball games so they can talk about what is going on in the game and how to make the correct modifications.

